        " \n \n \n \nRESEARCHER - PLEG19033\nClosing Date: 2024-03-26\nAssignment Type: Fixed Term Contract\nDivision: OCW-Office of the Chief Whip Division (2019)\nDepartment: OS-Office of the Chief Whip (2019)\nProvince: Gauteng\n\nPurpose:\n \nResponsibilities\nProvide an effective research and advisory service to allocated Caucus Members, Committees of Council as well as Council in general\nAdvise Caucus Members in the Oversight Committees through monitoring and evaluating whether the implementation of departmental business plans to enhance the Caucus Members on the role and functions of the Oversight\nCompile and present reports to ensure that improved decision making by the Caucus take place\nIdentify and initiate research projects to ensure that the agenda of Committee(s) is influenced is followed to the latter and address the purpose as set out in the Terms of Reference\nConduct independent research on behalf of the Caucus to ensure that research projects are delivered according to Caucus requirements and influence Caucus recommendations to Council\nDisseminate research information to ensure improved decision making and continuous enhancement of the quality of support provided to the Caucus\nDevelop and maintain relations and networks to build and maintain relationships and networks with other research professionals to enhance the quality of research conducted in the Legislature\nRecommend research capability and skills, when required, based on the Caucus requirements and Committee requests for negotiation and contracting\n \nJob Requirements\nRelevant Business Degree or relevant equivalent NQF Level 7 qualification\n1 - 3 years' experience in a similar environment and ability to manage a number of projects simultaneously\nProven track record in research and analysis\nKnowledge of Local Government Legislation\n \n \nEnquiries: Tel: 0860 54 3000\n \nCandidates may be requested to submit proof of the NQF level applicable to the qualifications they have obtained.\n \nShould candidates not be informed of the outcome of the application within six weeks of the closing date, it should be regarded as having been unsuccessful. The City of Ekurhuleni subscribes to the principles of the Employment Equity Act and reserves the right to appoint, not appoint or to appoint laterally.\n \nPreferred:\nRemuneration: R 706842.12 to R - Total Cost of Company per annum\nContact:\nTelephone:\n \nAPPLY NOW!\n \n \n \n \n ",
        "MEDIA OFFICER - PLEG19043\nClosing Date: 2024-03-26\nAssignment Type: Fixed Term Contract\nDivision: OCW-Office of the Chief Whip Division (2019)\nDepartment: OS-Office of the Chief Whip (2019)\nProvince: Gauteng\n\nPurpose:\n \nResponsibilities\nWork with the public relations and other media professionals to support the planning, implementation and evaluation of CoE's media based activities\nPlan, organise, direct, research, control and develop media content for the Department to ensure that the media system is up to date and that any changes are recorded\nEnsure that completed work adhere to governance and legislative requirements\nAdhere to specified standards, policies and SOPs to prevent and reduce wastage on financial resources and escalate associated risk\nContribute to a culture, which builds rewarding relationships and enables exceptional customer service and ethical conduct by being a good example\n \nJob Requirements\nA Degree in media related studies\n1 - 3 years' experience in a similar environment\n \n \nEnquiries: Tel: 0860 54 3000\n \nCandidates may be requested to submit proof of the NQF level applicable to the qualifications they have obtained.\n \nShould candidates not be informed of the outcome of the application within six weeks of the closing date, it should be regarded as having been unsuccessful. The City of Ekurhuleni subscribes to the principles of the Employment Equity Act and reserves the right to appoint, not appoint or to appoint laterally.\n \nPreferred:\nRemuneration: R 636423.92 to R - Total Cost of Company per annum\nContact:\nTelephone:\n \nAPPLY NOW!",
